com.hexoskin.hsapi_android

Class HexoskinAPI

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hexoskin.hsapi_android.swig.hsapi_callback
      • com.hexoskin.hsapi_android.HexoskinAPI

  • public class HexoskinAPI
extends com.hexoskin.hsapi_android.swig.hsapi_callback
    The HexoskinAPI helps you decode the data coming from the Hexoskin Device. It will also help you to send the right command to the Hexoskin Device when you need for example to know the battery level.

    • Constructor Detail

      • HexoskinAPI

        public HexoskinAPI(HexoskinDataListener dataListener,
                   HexoskinCommandWriter commandWriter,
                   HexoskinLogListener logListener)
        Create the HexoskinAPI responsible for decoding the bytes coming from the Hexoskin. Also responsible to let you know the appropriate command to send to the Hexoskin. For example, when asking for battery information, the API will call the HexoskinCommandWriter with the appropriate bytes to send to the socket in order for the Hexoskin to reply with the battery information via your input socket stream
        Parameters:
        dataListener - A listener for biometric data
        commandWriter - Responsible to send the command bytes to the Hexoskin (should be writing to the output stream of your bluetooth socket)
        logListener - A listener for log information

    • Method Detail

      • Init

        public int Init()
        Should call this to initialize the HexoskinAPI. Do this after you have successfully connected to the Hexoskin AND have successfully gotten the input/output streams from the socket This will initiliaze the API state
        Returns:
        -1 if initialization failed, otherwise all good to go

      • Uninit

        public void Uninit()

      • enableBluetoothTransmission

        public int enableBluetoothTransmission()
        The Hexoskin Device bluetooth will only transmit data for 1 minute. After 1 minute, the Hexoskin Device stops the bluetooth transmission. To keep the bluetooth transmission, call this function at fixed period. Call this method after you have successfully initialize the HexoskinAPI for Hexoskin Device to start transmitting data
        Returns:
        -1 if error

      • setRealTimeMode

        public int setRealTimeMode(boolean ecgOff,
                           boolean respOff,
                           boolean accOff,
                           boolean ppgOff,
                           boolean tempOff)
        Call this method after you have successfully initialize the HexoskinAPI. This is to control which kind of data you want the Hexoskin Device to send. The Hexoskin Device will always send the high level data such as Heart Rate, Breathing Rate, etc. For the RAW level data such as ECG, PPG, etc you can control which data you would like the Hexoskin Device to send.
        Parameters:
        ecgOff - true to not send ECG data
        respOff - true to not send Respiration RAW data
        accOff - true to not send Acceleration data
        ppgOff - true to not send PPG data
        tempOff - true to not send Temperature data
        Returns:
        -1 if error

      • getBatteryLevel

        public int getBatteryLevel()
        Will get the battery level of the Hexoskin.
        Returns:
        -1 when didn't successfully read the battery level otherwise a value from 0-100
